page_title: 'How to use blocklists with Azure OpenAI Service'
page_description: Learn how to use blocklists with Azure OpenAI Service
chunk_content: Prerequisites- An Azure subscription. Create one for free.- Once you have your Azure subscription, create an Azure OpenAI resource in the Azure portal to get your token, key and endpoint. Enter a unique name for your resource, select the subscription you entered on the application form, select a resource group, supported region, and supported pricing tier. Then select Create. - The resource takes a few minutes to deploy. After it finishes, select go to resource. In the left pane, under Resource Management, select Subscription Key and Endpoint. The endpoint and either of the keys are used to call APIs.- Azure CLI installed- cURL installed
